# run_cfa_sem.py

import os
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from semopy import Model, calc_stats, report
from semopy.inspector import inspect
from scipy.stats import norm

# ─── CONFIGURATION ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
DATA_PATH  = "C:/sasdata/clean_data.csv"
EXPORT_DIR = "C:/sasdata/"
os.makedirs(EXPORT_DIR, exist_ok=True)

# ─── LOAD DATA ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
df = pd.read_csv(DATA_PATH)

# ─── MODEL SPECIFICATIONS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
cfa_desc = """
PU  =~ PU1 + PU2 + PU3
EU  =~ EU1 + EU2 + EU3
ATT =~ ATT1 + ATT2 + ATT3
SN  =~ SN1 + SN2
PBC =~ PBC1 + PBC2 + PBC3
BI  =~ BI1 + BI2 + BI3
"""
sem_desc = cfa_desc + """
ATT ~ PU + EU
PU  ~ EU
BI  ~ ATT + PU + SN + PBC
"""

constructs    = ["PU","EU","ATT","SN","PBC","BI"]
observed_vars = [c for c in df.columns if c not in constructs]

# ─── 1) FIT CFA-ONLY MODEL ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
print("🔍 Fitting CFA-only measurement model…")
cfa_model = Model(cfa_desc)
cfa_model.fit(df)
cfa_params = inspect(cfa_model, std_est=True)
cfa_fit    = calc_stats(cfa_model)

# ─── 2) FIT FULL SEM MODEL ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
print("🔍 Fitting combined CFA+SEM model…")
sem_model = Model(sem_desc)
sem_model.fit(df)
sem_params = inspect(sem_model, std_est=True)
sem_fit    = calc_stats(sem_model)

# ─── 3) MODEL FIT INDICES (Table 16) ────────────────────────────────────────
def extract_indices(fit_df):
    row = fit_df.loc["Value"]
    chi2, dfv = float(row["chi2"]), float(row["DoF"])
    return {
        "Chi-square/df": round(chi2/dfv, 3),
        "RMSEA":         round(float(row["RMSEA"]), 3),
        "CFI":           round(float(row["CFI"]),   3),
        "TLI":           round(float(row["TLI"]),   3),
    }

cfa_idx = extract_indices(cfa_fit)
sem_idx = extract_indices(sem_fit)

fit_table = pd.DataFrame({
    "Fit Index":         list(cfa_idx.keys()),
    "Recommended": [
        "≤ 3.00",
        "≤ 0.08 (reasonable); < 0.05 (excellent)",
        "≥ 0.85; ≥ 0.90; ≥ 0.95",
        "≥ 0.85; ≥ 0.90; ≥ 0.95"
    ],
    "Measurement Model": list(cfa_idx.values()),
    "Structural Model":  list(sem_idx.values())
})
fit_table.to_csv(os.path.join(EXPORT_DIR, "Table16_ModelFitComparison.csv"), index=False)
print("\n📐 Table 16 – Model Fit Comparison")
print(fit_table)

# ─── 4) CFA LOADINGS & RELIABILITY ─────────────────────────────────────────
cfa_load = cfa_params[
    (cfa_params.op == "~") &
    (cfa_params.rval.isin(constructs)) &
    (cfa_params.lval.isin(observed_vars))
].copy()
cfa_load.rename(columns={
    "lval":"Observed","rval":"Latent",
    "Est. Std":"Loading","Std. Err":"SE","z-value":"t-value"
}, inplace=True)
cfa_load = cfa_load[["Observed","Latent","Loading","SE","t-value"]]
cfa_load.to_csv(os.path.join(EXPORT_DIR, "CFA_Loadings.csv"), index=False)
print("\n📋 CFA Loadings")
print(cfa_load)

# Composite Reliability & AVE
cr_ave = []
for L in constructs:
    xs   = pd.to_numeric(cfa_load.loc[cfa_load.Latent==L,"Loading"], errors="coerce").dropna()
    errs = 1 - xs**2
    cr   = xs.sum()**2/(xs.sum()**2 + errs.sum()) if len(xs)>0 else np.nan
    ave  = (xs**2).sum()/len(xs) if len(xs)>0 else np.nan
    cr_ave.append((L, cr, ave))
df_cr_ave = pd.DataFrame(cr_ave, columns=["Construct","CR","AVE"])

# ─── 5) PREDICT LATENT SCORES & CORRELATIONS ────────────────────────────────
factors = sem_model.predict_factors(df)
corr    = factors[constructs].corr()

# Compute MSV & MaxR(H)
msv_list, maxrh_list = [], []
for L in constructs:
    off = corr.loc[L].drop(L).dropna()
    mr  = off.max() if len(off)>0 else np.nan
    msv_list.append(mr**2 if pd.notna(mr) else np.nan)
    maxrh_list.append(1/(1-mr**2) if pd.notna(mr) and mr**2<1 else np.nan)
df_cr_ave["MSV"], df_cr_ave["MaxR(H)"] = msv_list, maxrh_list

# ─── 6) ASSEMBLE Table 18 ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
table18 = df_cr_ave.set_index("Construct")

# ensure AVE numeric
table18["AVE"] = table18["AVE"].astype(float)

# add placeholder cols for constructs
for c in constructs:
    table18[c] = np.nan

# fill columns j ≤ i
for i_idx, i in enumerate(constructs):
    ave_val = table18.at[i,"AVE"]
    for j_idx, j in enumerate(constructs):
        if j_idx < i_idx:
            table18.at[i,j] = corr.at[i,j]
        elif j_idx == i_idx:
            table18.at[i,j] = np.sqrt(ave_val)
        # else leave NaN

# round and reorder
table18 = table18.reset_index()
for col in ["CR","AVE","MSV","MaxR(H)"] + constructs:
    table18[col] = pd.to_numeric(table18[col], errors="coerce").round(3)
cols = ["Construct","CR","AVE","MSV","MaxR(H)"] + constructs
table18 = table18[cols]

table18.to_csv(os.path.join(EXPORT_DIR, "Table18_ModelValidity.csv"), index=False)
print("\n📋 Table 18 – Model Validity & Reliability")
print(table18)

# ─── 7) SEM PATHS & EXPORT ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
sem_paths = sem_params[sem_params.op=="~"].copy()
sem_paths["t-value"] = pd.to_numeric(sem_paths["z-value"], errors="coerce")
sem_paths["p-value"] = sem_paths["t-value"].apply(lambda z:2*(1-norm.cdf(abs(z))) if pd.notna(z) else np.nan)
sem_paths.rename(columns={"lval":"Dependent","rval":"Independent","Estimate":"β"}, inplace=True)
sem_paths = sem_paths[["Dependent","Independent","β","t-value","p-value"]]
sem_paths.to_csv(os.path.join(EXPORT_DIR, "SEM_Paths.csv"), index=False)
print("\n📈 SEM Path Coefficients")
print(sem_paths)

# ─── 8) HYPOTHESIS TESTING & EXPORT ─────────────────────────────────────────
hypo_results = []
for label, D, I in [
    ("H1: ATT → BI","BI","ATT"),
    ("H2: PU → BI","BI","PU"),
    ("H3: PU → ATT","ATT","PU"),
    ("H4: EU → ATT","ATT","EU"),
    ("H5: EU → PU","PU","EU"),
    ("H6: SN → BI","BI","SN"),
    ("H7: PBC → BI","BI","PBC")
]:
    row    = sem_paths[(sem_paths.Dependent==D)&(sem_paths.Independent==I)].iloc[0]
    status = "Supported" if row["p-value"]<0.05 else "Not Supported"
    hypo_results.append((label, row.β, row["t-value"], row["p-value"], status))

df_hypo = pd.DataFrame(hypo_results, columns=["Hypothesis","β","t-value","p-value","Status"])
df_hypo.to_csv(os.path.join(EXPORT_DIR, "Hypothesis_Tests.csv"), index=False)
print("\n🧪 Hypothesis Testing Results")
print(df_hypo)

import pandas as pd
from graphviz import Digraph
from IPython.display import Image, display

# 1) Hypothesis results
df_hypo = pd.DataFrame([
    ("H1: ATT → BI", 0.945, 2.929743, 0.003392425, "Supported"),
    ("H2: PU → BI", -0.107, -0.369135, 0.7120273,  "Not Supported"),
    ("H3: PU → ATT", 0.425, 3.000022, 0.002699604, "Supported"),
    ("H4: EU → ATT", 0.968, 5.146332, 0.000000,     "Supported"),
    ("H5: EU → PU",  0.718, 5.275051, 0.000000,     "Supported"),
    ("H6: SN → BI",  0.266, 3.783873, 0.000154407,  "Supported"),
    ("H7: PBC → BI", 0.174, 1.953490, 0.051000,     "Not Supported"),
], columns=["Hypothesis","β","t-value","p-value","Status"])

# 2) Node positions & labels
nodes = {
    "EU":  ("0,3!",   "Perceived Ease of Use"),
    "PU":  ("0,2!",   "Perceived Usefulness"),
    "ATT": ("3,2.5!", "Attitude Towards Shared Micro-Modes"),
    "SN":  ("1.5,1!", "Subjective Norm"),
    "PBC": ("3,1!",   "Perceived Behavioral Control"),
    "BI":  ("6,2!",   "Intention to Adopt Shared Micro-Modes")
}

# 3) Helpers
def sig_stars(p):
    if p < 0.001: return "***"
    if p < 0.01:  return "**"
    if p < 0.05:  return "*"
    return ""
def edge_style(p):
    return "solid" if p < 0.05 else "dashed"

# 4) Build the Graphviz diagram
g = Digraph("SEM", engine="neato", format="png")
g.graph_attr.update(
    splines="ortho",
    overlap="false",
    margin="0.1",
    dpi="300"
)
g.node_attr.update(
    shape="box",
    style="rounded,filled",
    fillcolor="white",
    fontsize="10",
    penwidth="1.2",
    margin="0.2,0.1"
)
g.edge_attr.update(
    fontcolor="black",
    labelfontsize="10"
)

# 4a) Add nodes
for code, (pos, label) in nodes.items():
    g.node(code, label, pos=pos)

# 4b) Add edges
for _, row in df_hypo.iterrows():
    src, dst = [s.strip() for s in row["Hypothesis"].split(": ")[1].split("→")]
    lbl = f"{row['β']:.3f}{sig_stars(row['p-value'])}"
    g.edge(src, dst, xlabel=lbl, style=edge_style(row['p-value']))

# 5) Legend as plain-text node
legend_text = (
    "Legend:\n"
    "▶ Solid arrow: Significant path (p<0.05)\n"
    "▶ Dashed arrow: Insignificant path (p≥0.05)\n\n"
    "*** p<0.001\n"
    "**  p<0.01\n"
    "*   p<0.05"
)
g.node("legend", legend_text, shape="plaintext", fontsize="10", pos="3,0!")

# 6) Render & display inline
png = g.pipe()      # generates PNG bytes with neato
display(Image(png))

# 7) Save to file
g.render("SEM_path_diagram_with_legend", cleanup=True)
print("Saved SEM_path_diagram_with_legend.png")

import pandas as pd
from graphviz import Digraph
from IPython.display import Image, display

# ─── 1) Hypothesis test results ────────────────────────────────────────────
df_hypo = pd.DataFrame([
    ("H1: ATT → BI", 0.945,  2.929743, 0.003392425, "Supported"),
    ("H2: PU → BI", -0.107, -0.369135, 0.7120273,   "Not Supported"),
    ("H3: PU → ATT", 0.425,  3.000022, 0.002699604, "Supported"),
    ("H4: EU → ATT", 0.968,  5.146332, 0.000000,     "Supported"),
    ("H5: EU → PU",  0.718,  5.275051, 0.000000,     "Supported"),
    ("H6: SN → BI",  0.266,  3.783873, 0.000154407,  "Supported"),
    ("H7: PBC → BI", 0.174,  1.953490, 0.051000,     "Not Supported"),
], columns=["Hypothesis","β","t-value","p-value","Status"])

# ─── 2) Node positions & labels ────────────────────────────────────────────
nodes = {
    "EU":  ("0,3!",   "Perceived Ease of Use"),
    "PU":  ("0,2!",   "Perceived Usefulness"),
    "ATT": ("3,2.5!","Attitude Towards Shared Micro-Modes"),
    "SN":  ("1.5,1!", "Subjective Norm"),
    "PBC": ("3,1!",   "Perceived Behavioral Control"),
    "BI":  ("6,2!",   "Intention to Adopt Shared Micro-Modes")
}

# ─── 3) Helpers for significance & style ──────────────────────────────────
def sig_stars(p):
    if p < 0.001: return "***"
    if p < 0.01:  return "**"
    if p < 0.05:  return "*"
    return ""
def edge_style(p):
    return "solid" if p < 0.05 else "dashed"

# ─── 4) Build Graphviz Digraph ────────────────────────────────────────────
g = Digraph("SEM", engine="neato", format="png")
g.graph_attr.update(
    splines="ortho",
    overlap="false",
    margin="0.1",
    dpi="300"
)
g.node_attr.update(
    shape="box",
    style="rounded,filled",
    fillcolor="white",
    fontsize="10",
    penwidth="1.2",
    margin="0.2,0.1"
)
g.edge_attr.update(
    fontcolor="black",
    labelfontsize="10"
)

# 4a) Add nodes at fixed positions
for code, (pos, label) in nodes.items():
    g.node(code, label, pos=pos)

# 4b) Add edges, with special offset for PBC→BI label
for _, row in df_hypo.iterrows():
    src, dst = [s.strip() for s in row["Hypothesis"].split(": ")[1].split("→")]
    lbl = f"{row['β']:.3f}{sig_stars(row['p-value'])}"
    style = edge_style(row['p-value'])

    if src == "PBC" and dst == "BI":
        # offset label downwards so it's visible
        g.edge(src, dst,
               xlabel=lbl,
               style=style,
               xlp="4.5,1.2!")   # adjust as needed
    else:
        g.edge(src, dst, xlabel=lbl, style=style)

# ─── 5) Legend as plain-text node ─────────────────────────────────────────
legend_text = (
    "Legend:\n"
    "▶ Solid arrow: Significant path (p<0.05)\n"
    "▶ Dashed arrow: Insignificant path (p≥0.05)\n\n"
    "*** p<0.001\n"
    "**  p<0.01\n"
    "*   p<0.05"
)
g.node("legend", legend_text, shape="plaintext", fontsize="10", pos="3,0!")

# ─── 6) Render & display inline ──────────────────────────────────────────
png_data = g.pipe() 
display(Image(png_data))

# ─── 7) Save to file ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
g.render("SEM_path_diagram_with_legend", cleanup=True)
print("Saved SEM_path_diagram_with_legend.png")
